---
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
import { siteConfig } from '../config/site';

const playSteps = [
  {
    number: '1',
    title: 'Find TailTag players',
    description:
      'Look for participating fursuiters around the con. They may share their TailTag profile, wear a badge, or let people know they are catchable.',
  },
  {
    number: '2',
    title: 'Say hi respectfully',
    description:
      'Start with a compliment, a wave, a photo request, or a quick introduction. If they seem busy, resting, eating, performing, or moving through a crowd, give them space and try again later.',
  },
  {
    number: '3',
    title: 'Catch them in the app',
    description:
      'Once you have had a real interaction, add the catch in TailTag. Your catch becomes part of your weekend progress and helps you remember who you met.',
  },
  {
    number: '4',
    title: 'Keep exploring',
    description:
      'Complete daily tasks, earn achievements, revisit familiar faces, and discover fursuiters you might not have met otherwise.',
  },
];

const etiquette = [
  'Ask before taking photos, touching a suit, or joining an interaction.',
  'Do not block paths, follow people, interrupt handlers, or pressure anyone to participate.',
  'Let fursuiters rest, perform, talk privately, or get where they need to go.',
];

const challengeHighlights = [
  'Meet someone new',
  'Revisit a previous catch',
  'Find different kinds of characters',
  'Celebrate friendly con moments',
];
---

<section
  id="how-it-works"
  class="border-t border-card-border px-6 py-14 sm:py-20"
>
  <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl flex-col gap-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
      <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-primary">
        New player guide
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground sm:text-4xl">
        A friendly reason to say hello
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-5 text-base leading-7 text-foreground/75 sm:text-lg">
        TailTag is a social discovery game for furry conventions. Players find participating
        fursuiters, say hi, and add them to their catches in the app. Each catch helps build your
        con adventure, complete tasks, and unlock achievements.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground/75 sm:text-lg">
        TailTag is built around friendly, respectful interactions: compliments, photos, quick chats,
        and the little moments that make conventions memorable.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <div class="mb-8 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-end sm:justify-between">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-amber">How to play</p>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">Four simple steps at the con</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="max-w-xl text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/65">
          You can play casually or chase every challenge. Either way, the loop starts with one
          respectful interaction.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ol class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
        {
          playSteps.map((step) => (
            <li class="rounded-lg border border-card-border bg-background-elevated p-5">
              <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="flex h-9 w-9 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary text-sm font-bold text-background">
                  {step.number}
                </span>
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">{step.title}</h4>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/70">{step.description}</p>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[1.05fr_0.95fr] lg:items-start">
      <section class="rounded-lg border border-card-border bg-card p-6 sm:p-7">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-primary">Why it helps</p>
        <h3 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">Less awkward, more memorable</h3>
        <div class="mt-5 space-y-4 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/72 sm:text-base sm:leading-7">
          <p>
            Conventions can be exciting, but starting conversations can still be hard. TailTag gives
            you a reason to approach someone without making it awkward.
          </p>
          <p>
            Instead of wondering what to say, you have a shared game, a simple opener, and a
            low-pressure way to connect. For new attendees, that can turn the con from a place full
            of strangers into a weekend full of small, friendly moments.
          </p>
          <p>
            TailTag is not designed to be a replacement for real conversation. It helps make more of
            those conversations happen.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-lg border border-card-border bg-card p-6 sm:p-7">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-amber">Con etiquette</p>
        <h3 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">
          The catch matters less than kindness
        </h3>
        <ul class="mt-5 space-y-4">
          {
            etiquette.map((item) => (
              <li class="flex gap-3 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/72 sm:text-base sm:leading-7">
                <span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-amber" />
                <span>{item}</span>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-5 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/65">
          A missed catch is fine. A good interaction matters more than game progress.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <section class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-card-border bg-background-elevated">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[0.9fr_1.1fr]">
        <div class="bg-accent p-6 sm:p-8">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-primary">
            Example first catch
          </p>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">From quick hello to familiar face</h3>
        </div>
        <div
          class="space-y-4 p-6 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/72 sm:p-8 sm:text-base sm:leading-7"
        >
          <p>
            You are walking through the hotel lobby and spot a fursuiter whom you'd like to meet.
            You walk up to them, wave, compliment their character, and ask whether they would be up
            for a photo for TailTag.
          </p>
          <p>
            They say yes. After the photo, you open TailTag, add the catch, and see it count toward
            your daily challenge.
          </p>
          <p>
            Later that weekend, you recognize them again at another meetup. Now they aren't just
            another fursuiter; they're someone you have already met and can catch up with!
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="mb-8 max-w-2xl">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-primary">
          Daily challenges and achievements
        </p>
        <h3 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">Small goals for a bigger weekend</h3>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/70 sm:text-base sm:leading-7">
          TailTag gives you reasons to keep exploring without forcing you into one play style. A few
          meaningful catches can matter just as much as a full collection.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
        {
          challengeHighlights.map((highlight) => (
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-card-border bg-card px-4 py-5 text-sm font-semibold text-foreground/85">
              {highlight}
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      class="rounded-lg border border-card-border bg-primary px-6 py-8 text-center text-background sm:px-8"
    >
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Ready to play at your next con?</h3>
      <p
        class="mx-auto mt-3 max-w-2xl text-sm leading-6 text-background/80 sm:text-base sm:leading-7"
      >
        Join TailTag and make your next convention easier to explore, easier to remember, and easier
        to share with new friends.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-col justify-center gap-3 sm:flex-row">
        <a
          href="#download"
          class="inline-flex min-h-11 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-background px-5 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-foreground transition-colors hover:bg-accent hover:no-underline"
        >
          Download TailTag
        </a>
        <a
          href={siteConfig.links.telegramGroup}
          class="inline-flex min-h-11 items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-background/30 px-5 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-background transition-colors hover:bg-background/10 hover:no-underline"
        >
          <Icon
            name="simple-icons:telegram"
            class="h-4 w-4"
          />
          <span>Join the TailTag Players Telegram group</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</section>
